<h1>Directory of Signing with Babies Resources</h1>

    <p>
        <a href="/">Home</a> >
            <a href="/Science">Science</a>  >             <a href="/Science/Social_Sciences">Social Sciences</a>  >             <a href="/Science/Social_Sciences/Linguistics">Linguistics</a>  >             <a href="/Science/Social_Sciences/Linguistics/Languages">Languages</a>  >             <a href="/Science/Social_Sciences/Linguistics/Languages/Natural">Natural</a>  >             <a href="/Science/Social_Sciences/Linguistics/Languages/Natural/Sign_Languages">Sign Languages</a>  >             <a href="/Science/Social_Sciences/Linguistics/Languages/Natural/Sign_Languages/Signing_with_Babies">Signing with Babies</a>         </p>

<p><p>For sites related to augmenting language input to include signs in order to elicit earlier language development from Hearing children.</p></p>


<h2>Resources in This Category</h2>
<ul>

    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.australianbabyhands.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Australian Baby Hands</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.australianbabyhands.com/</strong></font> <br /> Auslan-based system for teaching babies manual communication before they become verbal.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.babies-and-sign-language.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Babies and Sign Language</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.babies-and-sign-language.com/</strong></font> <br /> Tips, articles, glossary photos, online videos.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.mybabyfingers.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Baby Fingers</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.mybabyfingers.com/</strong></font> <br /> Baby sign classes in the New York City Metropolitan area for families with young pre-lingual hearing children. Course description and schedule, local events, FAQ, links.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.mybabycantalk.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Baby Hands Productions</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.mybabycantalk.com/</strong></font> <br /> Video series for teaching babies to sign. Site provides information for parents and an online sign dictionary.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://lovelanguageforbabies.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Baby Sing and Sign</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://lovelanguageforbabies.com/</strong></font> <br /> Offers books and CDs to teach babies sign language through song. Also provides classes in the Kansas City area of the United States.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.handyexpressions.co.uk/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Handy Expressions</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.handyexpressions.co.uk/</strong></font> <br /> Baby signing tutorials, galleries and information about baby sign language history, research, training, teaching and baby signing classes in Gloucester, UK.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.hoptosignaroo.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Hop to Signaroo</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.hoptosignaroo.com/</strong></font> <br /> American Sign Language for hearing parents and their hearing babies. Classes taught by Nancy Hanauer in Seattle, Washington.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.kindersigns.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>KinderSigns</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.kindersigns.com/</strong></font> <br /> Free and commercial lessons on how to sign with babies plus links to research and resources on the subject.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.mysmarthands.ca/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>My Smart Hands</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.mysmarthands.ca/</strong></font> <br /> Provides instruction in ASL signing. Locations in Ontario as well as throughout the US and interactive online classes starting in January 2010.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.signbabies.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Sign Babies</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.signbabies.com/</strong></font> <br /> Articles, stories from parents, discussion forums, tips on finding a good class locally, and products.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.sign2me.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Sign with Your Baby</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.sign2me.com/</strong></font> <br /> Teaches hearing parents how to begin two-way communication with their hearing babies through sign language before their infants can speak. Instructional products and tools suitable for use with toddlers as young as 6-8 months.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.sign-a-song.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Sign-A-Song</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.sign-a-song.com/</strong></font> <br /> A musical introduction to sign language for babies and their parents. Workshops offered in Brookly, New York.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.signingsmart.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Signing Smart</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.signingsmart.com/</strong></font> <br /> Playclasses for hearing babies and toddlers, with locations throughout the northeastern United States. Also offers education for child care center staff wishing to integrate baby sign into their programs.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.singandsign.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Sing and Sign</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.singandsign.com/</strong></font> <br /> Videos for teaching British Baby Sign through music, and classes offered throughout the United Kingdom. Members can access an online dictionary and discussion forum.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.tinyfingers.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Tiny Fingers</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.tinyfingers.com/</strong></font> <br /> Independent curriculum offers videos and teaching kits. Classes for hearing babies, toddlers and their parents in the greater Washington, DC area.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://tinytalk.co.uk/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>TinyTalk</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://tinytalk.co.uk/</strong></font> <br /> Classes and resources for parents and their babies in the United Kingdom and Australia.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.tinytalk.com.au/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Tinytalk</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.tinytalk.com.au/</strong></font> <br /> Videos and other products for baby sign. Classes for parents and babies, held throughout Australia.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.weehands.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>WeeHands</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.weehands.com/</strong></font> <br /> Classes and workshops for babies, toddlers and preschool children. Many locations in Ontario, with additional locations in the rest of Canada and a few in the United States.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.angelfire.com/zine/babysigns/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>World of Baby Signs</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.angelfire.com/zine/babysigns/</strong></font> <br /> Step by step instructions teaching how to communicate with your baby using signs.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://groups.yahoo.com/group/signwithyourbaby/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Yahoo Club: Signing With Your Baby</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://groups.yahoo.com/group/signwithyourbaby/</strong></font> <br /> Message board for shaing experiences and advice.</p>
    </li>	
</ul>

